TY  - JOUR
AU  - Ahn, David S.
T1  - Ambiguity Without a State Space
PY  - 2008
Y1  - 2008/01/01
DO  - 10.1111/j.1467-937X.2007.00473.x
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 75
IS  - 1
SP  - 3
EP  - 28
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - Many decisions involve both imprecise probabilities and intractable states of the world. Objective expected utility assumes unambiguous probabilities; subjective expected utility assumes a completely specified state space. This paper analyses a third domain of preference: sets of consequential lotteries. Using this domain, we develop a theory of objective ambiguity without explicit reference to any state space. We characterize a representation that integrates a non-linear transformation of first-order expected utility with respect to a second-order measure. The concavity of the transformation and the weighting of the measure capture ambiguity aversion. We propose a definition for comparative ambiguity aversion.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1467-937X.2007.00473.x
ER  - 



