AB  - It is with great sorrow that we record the unexpected death in November 2007 of our editorial board member Antoni Calvó-Armengol at the age of 37. Apart from the tremendous personal loss to his wife and young children, other family, colleagues and friends, this is a great loss to the economics community in general, and to the Review of Economic Studies in particular. He was an outstanding researcher (coincidentally, one of his papers is published in this issue) and a warm and enthusiastic friend to many of us. We shall not be able to replace him.
